- ✅ Creates reactive calculation using `reaction::calc` 
- ✅ Returns calculated result using the function call operator
- ✅ Properly handles the reactive dependency chain
- ✅ Follows the reaction library patterns shown in the reference materials

The code demonstrates proper usage of the reaction library's reactive programming paradigm where changes to `reactive_a` or `reactive_b` would automatically trigger recalculation of the result.

